    // #28: ParadoxIntro

    void passage28_Init()
    {
        this.Passages[@"ParadoxIntro"] = new StoryPassage(@"ParadoxIntro", new string[] { "INTRO", }, passage28_Main);
    }

    IStoryThread passage28_Main()
    {
        //yield return lineBreak(); //hr tag
        using (styleScope("bold", true))
        {
            yield return text("GENERATION III: You Cant Stop Progress");
        }
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak(); //hr tag
        yield return lineBreak();
        using (styleScope("bold", true))
        {
            yield return text("A Brighter Future");
        }
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"While the discovery of my family's experiments and journals would cement my scientific ambitions for years to come, I had never actually met them. I was too young to remember the disappearance of my brilliant progenitor. To lose a parent and then another to the subsequent dementia that followed was more folly than one child should ever have to bear. I was shielded from this reality, rushed away to Vienna, where I was consumed by my studies until my twenty-first year. It was only at my partner's insistence that I decided to settle my inheritance.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"I remember being stunned as I arrived by train on a mid-summer's evening. I do not know what I expected from the anecdotes my nanny had relayed to me, but it  was not the bustling cityscape that greeted me. As the sun dipped into the forest, the glimmer of modern steel light fixtures amplified the urban luminescence. My delighted spouse and I enjoyed a quiet ride in our steamer car, which offered us a chance to observe the idyllic community and decidedly pleasant folk enjoying the convenience of electricity and steam turbine technology.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"The estate appeared untouched by years of vacancy; recently pruned brambles and ivy adorned the iron gate and the expansive grounds were immaculate. A caretaker of great age and a small housekeeping staff greeted us. Although updating the grounds to the more modern standard of the nearby town would prove a daunting task, the servants’ warm reception allayed our remaining anxieties. Upon discovery of my family's laboratory, what had been planned as a mere visit received an indefinite extension.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"When I spoke of my family's history of experimentation, I was rarely met with indifference but more often firm words of encouragement. It appeared that this region, so rife with abnormal progress, viewed my theories as rudimentary but delightfully avant-garde. Even when I expounded upon dark rituals and the grotesque, they encouraged further exploration and referred me to the newly constructed University.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text("This caused me severe consternation. Was this not what I wanted — a clear path to" +
            "wards scientific enlightenment and support of my family\'s landmark ideas? Why di" +
            "d their lack of friction vex me so? Did they view my illustrious work as trivial" +
            "? ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text("It was this grim realization that strengthened my will. If these craven modernist" +
            "s wanted more, then so be it! I would push the limits of science further than ev" +
            "er before and damn the consequences!");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return link("Click to Continue...", "TimeTravelEvent", null);
        yield return lineBreak();
        if (Vars.townname == "debug")
        {
            yield return text("v1.0");
        }
        Vars.accolade = macros1.either(12, 13);
        Vars.timemistake = macros1.either(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8);
        yield break;
    }


