        yield return text(@"I hope you will indulge my brief melancholic digression, for even my stern disposition was reduced to sobbing when I discovered the grim remnants of what was once a burgeoning village. I knew of the tragedy, having received several letters urging me to delay my visit until the conflict had been resolved. However, I felt compelled to see the destruction with my own eyes, and even braved the last vestiges of war to do so. If only I had taken heed of their warning...");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"The all-encompassing destruction had blackened the fields, leaving the land ashen and emaciated. The once-grand estate was now in shambles; a dilapidated husk of its former intimidating presence. I wept for what seemed like hours amongst the dust and rubble. While I was still heir to a considerable fortune with diverse business interests, I was struck by the sentimental weight of such a loss.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text("However, fortune would soon shine its myriad gaze upon me.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"I was joined by my cousins and we shared our grief at a hotel in Budapest for several days. It was there that an unexpected messenger arrived with a small brown package. Inside, the executor of our parents’ affairs had included the remaining articles of interest salvaged from the mansion. As if preserved for this moment, there was a leather journal seemingly untouched by the flames. Upon opening the tome, a weathered sheet of parchment fell to the table. ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text("It was a map!");
        yield return lineBreak();
