    // .............
    // #151: IntroMartial-Monarchists

    void passage151_Init()
    {
        this.Passages[@"IntroMartial-Monarchists"] = new StoryPassage(@"IntroMartial-Monarchists", new string[] { "INTRO", }, passage151_Main);
    }

    IStoryThread passage151_Main()
    {
        using (styleScope("bold", true))
        {
            yield return text("GENERATION II: Plagued by Conflict");
        }
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak(); //hr tag
        yield return text(@"If one can call the prospect of perpetual conflict stabilizing, my life settled into a somewhat steady routine. During the day, the sound of distant gunfire rumbled through the halls of my estate as silver plumes of smoke billowed beyond the mountainous horizon, casting tendril-like shadows across the land — a constant reminder of civil war. At night, the rare spectacle of an explosion brightening the sky surprised me with how viscerally I reacted.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"Soldiers in their bright regalia keep watch over the town from a newly erected outpost, waving the brilliant orange flag of royalty. The Monarchy had claimed victory from afar after stationing their ranks across the region, but as scuffles remained constant, this declaration was all pomp without substance. The Monarchy drafted citizens into their ranks and levied penalties against those who showed disloyalty.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"The inference that one of my standing should owe a debt of servitude to those who already tax my earnings into oblivion was enough to make me spill my tea. And to what end, I wondered? Could peace be mustered in a populace kept so distant from the individuals who ruled it? It was called the industrial revolution for a reason, was it not?");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"But, I must admit, the safety that the Monarchy afforded appealed to my pocketbook. Appeasing the Monarchy would ensure money and influence, but it also appeared — for better or ill — that royalty was distant enough to take little interest in our experimentations unless they provided direct benefit to themselves, whereas the Separatists were interested in knowledge and were desperate to explore all scientific options available to them to turn the tide. However, their frail sensibilities would not so easily accept my experimentations. ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"Ah, to be left to one's own devices or to be famously scrutinized, reviled, and revered in equal measure! The decision weighed upon me so heavily it gave me mild indigestion during my evening banquets. What direction should I choose to advance my most important scientific work? ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        Vars.iou = 0;
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return link("Click to continue...", "GUNSAward", null);
        yield break;
    }

    // .............
    // #152: IntroMartial-Separatists

    void passage152_Init()
    {
        this.Passages[@"IntroMartial-Separatists"] = new StoryPassage(@"IntroMartial-Separatists", new string[] { "INTRO", }, passage152_Main);
    }

    IStoryThread passage152_Main()
    {
        using (styleScope("bold", true))
        {
            yield return text("GENERATION II: Down with the Monarchy");
        }
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak(); //hr tag
        yield return text(@"The length and difficulty of my journey was exacerbated by the ongoing conflict. Compounding this harried inconvenience, my spouse and I suffered the indignity of a lengthy interrogation by soldiers of the Separatist forces, who had imposed an unofficial martial government. ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"Peasants-turned-soldiers in their motley uniforms keep watch over the town from a newly erected outpost waving a sanguine flag. They spoke of freedom as they dug fresh graves in the cemetery; the wrought iron gates perpetually wreathed in lilies. I observed the daily horse-drawn carts, dragging the wounded towards ill-equipped infirmaries; my crimson reflection in the muddy ruts of unpaved highways.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"It was both in spite of and because of this brashness that I found myself drawn to the scrappy Separatist upstarts and their eagerness to fight for the capricious whims of the great unwashed. The Separatists were desperate for the advantages that my family's experimentations provided, and while hesitant over our methods, were willing to further our knowledge in return. Unfortunately, this relationship made them more entitled to levy accusations towards us.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(" ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"However, the influence of the throne was still absolute. If one could ingratiate themselves with the distracted Monarchy, their influence and money was on offer. The peasantry would be too discontent to focus on our more ""ambitious"" works. Unfortunately, unless experimentation directly benefited them, the Monarchy had no use for it.");
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return text(@"Ah, to be left to one's own devices or to be famously scrutinized, reviled, and revered in equal measure! The decision weighed upon me so heavily that I could scarcely enjoy my afternoon pastries. Neither could the muffled wailing coming from the cellar laboratory nor the distant clattering of gunfire at night calm my weary mind. What direction should I choose to advance my most important scientific work? ");
        yield return lineBreak();
        Vars.iou = 0;
        Vars.sepevent = macros1.either(1, 2);
        yield return lineBreak();
        yield return link("Click to continue...", "GUNSAward", null);
        yield break;
    }


